    "collapsible_content_pBrGf3": {
      "type": "collapsible-content",
      "blocks": {
        "collapsible_row_igiUxt": {
          "type": "collapsible-row-content",
          "settings": {
            "open": false,
            "heading": "Are Yealink phones compatible with all phone systems?",
            "icon": "check_box",
            "filled_icon": false,
            "row_content": "<p>Yes. Yealink phones use the open SIP standard, which makes them compatible with most hosted PBX, cloud VoIP, and on-premise phone systems. If you’re unsure, our team can confirm compatibility with your current setup before purchase.<br/><br/></p>",
            "page": ""
          },
          "blocks": {}
        },
        "collapsible_row_DVyWde": {
          "type": "collapsible-row-content",
          "settings": {
            "open": false,
            "heading": "Do Yealink phones support wireless connectivity like Wi-Fi and Bluetooth?",
            "icon": "check_box",
            "filled_icon": false,
            "row_content": "<p>Many Yealink models come with built-in Wi-Fi and Bluetooth (e.g. the T5W series), while others may require an optional USB dongle. This allows you to connect wirelessly to your network and pair with Bluetooth headsets or mobile devices.<br/><br/></p>",
            "page": ""
          },
          "blocks": {}
        },
        "collapsible_row_bfW97K": {
          "type": "collapsible-row-content",
          "settings": {
            "open": false,
            "heading": "Can I use a headset with Yealink phones?",
            "icon": "check_box",
            "filled_icon": false,
            "row_content": "<p>Yes. Yealink phones support both wired and wireless headsets. You can plug in a wired headset via the RJ9/USB ports, or use Bluetooth headsets on supported models. For DECT wireless headsets, Yealink phones are compatible with EHS (Electronic Hook Switch) adapters.</p>",
            "page": ""
          },
          "blocks": {}
        },
        "collapsible_row_Fm8qLb": {
          "type": "collapsible-row-content",
          "settings": {
            "open": false,
            "heading": "What is the difference between Yealink entry-level, mid-range, and premium phones?",
            "icon": "check_box",
            "filled_icon": false,
            "row_content": "<ul><li><strong>Entry-level models</strong> (e.g. T3 series) are affordable, reliable phones for basic business use.</li><li><strong>Mid-range models</strong> (e.g. T4 series) offer larger screens, faster performance, and more advanced features.</li><li><strong>Premium models</strong> (e.g. T5 series) include adjustable color displays, built-in Wi-Fi/Bluetooth, HD audio, and advanced call handling — ideal for executives and heavy users.</li></ul>",
            "page": ""
          },
          "blocks": {}
        }
      },
